    <item>
      <title>Home Microgreens Setup</title>
      <link>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/domesticity/domains/production/gardening/domains/home-gardening/domains/microgreens/texts/home-microgreens-setup/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/domesticity/domains/production/gardening/domains/home-gardening/domains/microgreens/texts/home-microgreens-setup/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Audience: beginners who want to grow microgreens indoors.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Learning goal: list the basic materials and steps for a simple home tray setup.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;materials&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#materials&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Link to this section&#34;&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;Materials&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;shallow tray with drainage&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;growing medium (coconut coir or potting mix)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;seeds labeled for microgreens&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;light source or sunny window&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;steps&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#steps&#34; class=&#34;heading-anchor&#34; aria-label=&#34;Link to this section&#34;&gt;¶&lt;/a&gt;Steps&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Fill the tray with a thin layer of medium and moisten it.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Scatter seeds evenly, then press gently into the surface.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Cover lightly and keep moist until germination.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Move to light and water from below if possible.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Check for understanding: Why is a shallow tray preferred for microgreens?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
